  "text": "The authors declare no conflicts of interest. The funders had no role in the design of the study; in the collection, analyses, or interpretation of data; in the writing of the manuscript, or in the decision to publish the results. Figure A1 . Plasma membrane topology of hCCK1R (upper panel) and hCCK2R (lower panel). Black circles filled with white letters indicate identical residues, gray circles indicate homologous residues. The dashed lines indicate disulfide bonds. Residues essential for agonist binding or CCK2R activation are in red boxes [CITATION_1] . Blue letters indicate residues that play a key role in receptor activation and readily oxidized by 1 O 2 [CITATION_2] . The green arrow in the lower panel indicates a site where a sequence of 69 residues is inserted due to a mis-spliced intron 4 [CITATION_3] .",
